**Step 3:** The two roots are:  
$$ x = \frac{ -3 + \sqrt{17} }{ 2 } \quad \text{and} \quad x = \frac{ -3 - \sqrt{17} }{ 2 } $$  
Both are real because the discriminant is positive (17 > 0).

